mory consumption\n- node disk read I/O consumption \n- node disk write I/O consumption \n- node disk space consumption\n\nAnomaly Cluster Description:\nHere is the RCA analysis result in plain English:\n\n```\n{\n  "Cluster 1": {\n    "Key Findings": [\n      "adservice-grpc experienced a sustained anomaly with count metric, occurring at 19:05:00 CST, 19:08:00 CST, and 19:09:00 CST.",\n      "adservice2.ts:8088 had a sustained anomaly with java_lang_GarbageCollector_LastGcInfo_memoryUsageAfterGc_committ metric, happening at 19:01:00 CST, 19:02:00 CST, 19:04:00 CST, 19:05:00 CST, and 19:08:00 CST.",\n      "node-5.currencyservice-2 had a sustained anomaly with container_ulimits_soft.max_open_files metric, occurring at 19:05:00 CST, 19:09:00 CST, 19:11:00 CST, and 19:13:00 CST."\n    ],\n    "Root Cause": "The root cause of the anomalies in Cluster 1 is likely related to adservice-grpc and adservice2.ts:8088 experiencing garbage collection issues, leading to increased load on node-5.currencyservice-2."\n  },\n  "Cluster 2": {\n    "Key Findings": [\n      "adservice-grpc experienced a single-point anomaly with count metric at 19:16:00 CST.",\n      "adservice2.ts:8088 had a single-point anomaly with java_lang_GarbageCollector_LastGcInfo_memoryUsageAfterGc_committ metric at 19:16:00 CST.",\n      "node-5.currencyservice-2 had a single-point anomaly with container_ulimits_soft.max_open_files metric at 19:16:00 CST."\n    ],\n    "Root Cause": "The root cause of the anomalies in Cluster 2 is likely related to adservice-grpc and adservice2.ts:8088 experiencing garbage collection issues, but this is an isolated event and not sustained."\n  },\n  "Cluster 3": {\n    "Key Findings": [\n      "node-5.currencyservice-2 had a sustained anomaly with container_ulimits_soft.max_open_files metric, occurring at 19:18:00 CST and 19:20:00 CST.",\n      "node-2 experienced a single-point anomaly with system.load.15 metric at 19:19:00 CST.",\n      "currencyservice-1 had a log anomaly a