ce showed istio_request_bytes.grpc.200.14.0 anomalies, possibly related to request processing."\n    ],\n    "Related Entities": [\n      "node-5.shippingservice-0",\n      "adservice-0.destination.frontend.adservice"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nRelevant Historical Incidents (if any):\n[Past Incident 1] (Score: 0.455)\nComponent: node-1 | Metrics: CPU, I/O, disk, load, memory, network, rr, rt\nSummary: Component: node-1\nEvent: node-1 failure at 2022-03-20 10:25:33\nSystem Type: Banking Microservice (node)\nSymptoms: node memory consumption; The `currencyservice-0` container on `node-5` showed a high number of anomalies across multiple memory metrics, including `container_memory_max_usage_MB`, `container_memory_usage_MB`, and `container_m; Frequent major page fault anomalies (`container_memory_failures.container.pgmajfault`) were observed for `currencyservice-0` throughout the incident window, indicating memory pressure forcing reads fr; Node-level metrics for `node-5` confirm the impact of memory swapping with anomalies in `system.io.r_await` (I/O wait time) and `system.io.r_s` (reads per second).\nAffected Metrics: CPU, I/O, disk, load, memory, network, rr, rt\nRoot Cause Category: The incident was caused by excessive memory consumption in the `currencyservice-0` container, which led to resource starvation on its host, `node-5`. \nFailure Pattern: The incident was caused by excessive memory consumption in the `currencyservice-0` container, which led to resource starvation on its host, `node-5`. The high memory usage triggered numerous major page faults (`pgmajfault`), resulting in heavy disk I/O and high I/O wait times on the node. This resource contention caused CPU throttling for the container and made the entire node intermittently unresponsive, as evidenced by ping failures. The provided ground truth incorrectly identifies the affected component as `node-1`, whereas all telemetry data points conclusively to `node-5` as the epicenter of the failure.\nMitigation Principles: 1. Investigate the `currencyservice` application for memory leaks or inefficient memory usage patterns. 2. Review and enforce stricter memory resource limits on the `currencyservice` deployment to prevent a single pod from impacting the entire node. 3. Enhance node-level alerting to trigger on high I/O wait and major page fault rates, in addition to memory usage, for earlier detection of resource starvation. 4. Correct the incident management process to ensure ground truth data is validated against telemetry during post-mortems.\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
